&gt; Last year a Juyo Token Niji Kunitoshi was taken in the same manner, it
&gt; was scanned by someone as being sent to Canada Customs, then it
&gt; vanished. There was a several week period in both cases of me having to
&gt; fight people who&#39;s computer screens told them something that wasn&#39;t
&gt; true, then finally they admitted the package vanished into thin air.
&gt; 
&gt; Last year they searched the warehouse several times without it turning
&gt; up, and when I said I was sending the police over, 15 minutes later the
&gt; sword appeared in some office where someone had &quot;mistakenly left it&quot;
&gt; after scanning that it was sent to customs.
&gt; 
&gt; My hope is that the same scam is being played again.
&gt; 
&gt; Obviously with the cost of a blade like this, it is not a trivial matter
&gt; and I feel kind of sick. Insurance says they will not cover it. 
&gt; 
&gt; Pictures of the blade are on my site as I have the paperwork.
&gt; 
&gt; It has gone missing or been stolen in the Toronto area. Lately there
&gt; has been a new study group formed in Toronto with a lot of attendees. It
&gt; is possible with the new dissemination of information there that there
&gt; is more knowledge about the value of these swords and so we&#39;re going to
&gt; start seeing more thefts. 
&gt; 
&gt; Here&#39;s the link to my site:
&gt; 
